In this article, Vice President Kamala Harris and Secretary Jennifer Granholm discuss their work on climate change and environmental justice. They highlight the importance of equity in addressing climate issues and the need for intersectionality in this movement. They also emphasize the role of young people in taking action and creating change. The conversation touches on various topics, such as the importance of clean energy jobs, the intersection between climate and maternal health, and the need to build coalitions and address systemic inequities.